ga|Serbo-Montenegrin First League]]. Upon the independence of Montenegro, and the establishment of a [[Montenegrin Football Association]], the league became disassociated with the Serbo-Montenegrin league and thus was given its present position.\n\nThe league played its first games of the season on August 12, 2006 and its final matches were played on May 26, 2007. On May 26, after their final match, [[FK Zeta]] were confirmed as the league's first ever champions under the new FA, and thus qualified as the country's first ever [[UEFA Champions League]] competitor.\n\n==Inaugural members==\n{{Location map+|Montenegro|float=right|width=300|caption=Location of the 2006\u201307 Montenegrin First League teams|places=\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.444805 |long=19.264441 |label=[[OFK Titograd Podgorica|Mladost]]<br />[[FK Budu\u0107nost Podgorica|Budu\u0107nost]] |position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.444805 |long=19.264441 |label=[[FK Kom|Kom]] |position=right}}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.365556 |long=19.331389 |label=[[FK De\u010di\u0107|De\u010di\u0107]] }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.355166 |long=18.756166 |label=[[FK Grbalj|Grbalj]] |position=left }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=43.04 |long=19.75 |label=[[FK Jedinstvo Bijelo Polje|Jedinstvo]] }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.838833 |long=19.870666 |label=[[FK Berane|Berane]] |position=left }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.285166 |long=18.837333 |label=[[FK Mogren|Mogren]]|position=right }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=43.351333 |long=19.3525 |label=[[FK Rudar Pljevlja|Rudar]] |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.203333 |long=18.938833 |label=[[OFK Petrovac|Petrovac]] |position=right }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.771666 |long=18.955 |label=[[FK Sutjeska Nik\u0161i\u0107|Sutjeska]] }}\n{{Location map~|Montenegro|lat=42.335 |long=19.231111 |label=[[FK Zeta|Zeta]] |position=left}}\n}}\nIn order of their 2005-06 league table position.\n\n===From the form